RelatedSentence: -- A Tennessee appellate court has reversed an award of summary judgment entered in favor of Illinois Central Railroad , finding that a prior settlement agreement reached between the defendant and an asbestosis plaintiff contained boilerplate language that did not sufficiently establish that the plaintiff was aware he could develop mesothelioma in the future .
